definition: to fret/to get impatient/to become anxious
to send out/to show (one's feeling)/to issue/to develop/to make a bundle of money/classifier for gunshots (rounds)

sentences.chinese: 臨牀上往往伴發急性膀胱炎。

sentences.english: There's no need to worry, for your husring knows how to fob the gang off.

sentences.english: And the fans of the home team had to accept it woefully with a heavy heart.

sentences.english: Don't try to hard , the best things come when you least expect them to .
sentences.chinese: 不要發急，最好的總會在最不經意的時候呈現。

sentences.english: I just want to love you do not fear harm.
sentences.chinese: 自己只是想不發急危險地去愛你。

sentences.english: We walked slowly, even happiness are worried.
